            <div type="commentary">
                <p>The stone was first published by Manganaro 1981 in association with <ref target="http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic2754">ISic2754</ref>, the two seemingly having been discovered together, or at least in close proximity; the letter forms are essentially identical, and the texts were probably cut by the same hand. Manganaro 1981 and Parke 1986 noted the further potential relevance of <ref target="http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic1040">ISic1040</ref>.</p>
